Universal Sea

I stood on the shore at night and felt an awesome fright
The sky and ground merged to one and the immensity of the sea terrified me
The cacophony of sound
The white noise and rolling waves
I again thought about what messages are irretrievably encoded in those waves
And imagined the entire universe the same way
Wavering between a fountain, a book, and a sea
1:03 AM
a single verse - the universe

This mystery will not end
This search for truth is fraught with error
This precious walk between death and life
Is filled with both awe and terror

One blind corner
Leads to two blind alleys
By now you’d expect the grand finale

Yet here I am
Still awake
Conscious of every breath I take

You say that God does not exist
Yet I sincerely ask - then why do we?

A random blur
A spontaneous out growth
A grandiose cruel cosmic joke
A fiction penned by some unknown author

“The universe” - is all you offer

And so I give you the benefit of the doubt
And labor away in calculation
Fields, strings, groups, codes, spheres, loops, and all other contortions

“The universe” - is all you say
Then carry on your merry way
And I envy you in your self satisfaction
As I ponder this “principle of least action”

And all my friends have grown and cried
Yet here I remain - with this resounding “why?”

Why me or you?
Or the universe?
I demand an answer in a single verse!

“ His command is only when He intends a thing that He says to it, “Be,” and it is.“
7:01 PM
a summary of cantor’s cathedral

a summary of the development of Cantor’s cathedral and where it fits into Billy’s Pilgrimage.

- after billy leaves the desert he enters the city of “new alexandria” - based on the ancient city of alexandria in egypt, as well as alexandria virginia, where i lived for a few years.

he finds himself in the company of a group of merchants - the head of them takes billy in as a guest and allows him to dwell in the back of his shop in exchange for a few hours work each day. The daughter of this merchant (based on a girl i fell in love with) runs an academy and takes a liking to billy - she invites him to a gathering she hosts called “the worlds fair”

it is there that billy encounters Sunyata and her guardian Omar Khayyam. They give him a book titled “cantor’s cathedral” - an odd book that chronicles the development of Euclid’s empire and the construction of the infinite cathedral.

—– in short, Euclid and his boyhood friend Georg Cantor have an intense lust for the infinite horizon and begin constructing an infinite structure where everyone inside roams in absolute silence. after an immense amount of time however the rule of silence can no longer be maintained and the echoes of speech between isolated peoples begin to travel through the infinite.

the poet omar khayyam and his nephew? (i’m not sure of the relationship yet) sunyata have found a way of escaping the cathedral
——-

it is after they escaped that they ended in new alexandria where sunyata shares a mutual friend with the merchant’s daughter. and it is through this mutual friend that billy meets the two and learns about the history of Euclid’s empire.

what makes things infinitely more complex is that Sunyata is actually the daughter of billy and the merchant’s daughter (as in the name i’d give to my daughter if i married the girl i fell in love with and we had a child….) only neither of them are really aware of this

nor do i know how it will play out in the development of the story

nor do i know exactly what that girl feels for me

nor does it really matter right now.

and that’s it i suppose….

oh yea! and because billy now knows about cantor and euclid’s empire - when he encounters the aged cantor in new alexandria he knows who he is.

the infinite cathedral of euclid and cantor is different than the infinite cathedral of cantor in new alexandria.

the former is a single structure with pillars stretched all across euclid’s plane. the latter is a normal cathedral, only that within each dust particle there is yet another cathedral….

“O God, I could be bounded in a nutshell and count myself a king of infinite space.” - Hamlet
4:21 PM
Dedication

Within these pages is a noble attempt in futility… The colossal infinity that stretches before and after. The places, names, forms and faces that have come to be and pass. Monuments erected and crumbled in the sand. Written works and novel ideas. No human book could contain the transformations of the echoes through time… And yet here I am, pen to paper, etching away. For whoever may find this, in whatever realm, time, or sphere. This humble work - is dedicated to you my dear.

And so we begin - somewhere after genesis…
4:16 PM
riding the asymptote

hovering, sailing transcendently the single dimensional line carrying upwards - imagine the wake left by a boat, or maybe an endless zipper. There were no increments of time or distance, just a continual tunneling further and further.

First wave - objects familiar to the senses. Diving through layers of epiphenomena, tables, chairs, faces, organs, tissue, cells, nerves, molecules, shells and energy levels, hadrons, quarks, fields, strings, manifolds, further still to points along the number line, ever closer to zero.

The thin verge of nonexistence ever approaching. It’s quite impossible to really know the amount of time that had passed - no periodic processes occured at such scales. The approaching became a desert and he a pilgrim - the null sun ever fixed on the horizion.

eras passed without the slightest indication of advancement.
