Billy’s proposal

—- a sudden and growing fancy —-

“Let me propose this modest venture… I say, as the winds of fate change course, we grasp this current state of disarray and escape the tyranny of the past chapters - having now turned to dust - discard those pages and venture out into the eternally uncertain.

First - a ship, a vessel, a carriage, free from as many restrictions as possible

Secondly - a crew. A cook, some radio equipment, weapons, maps, wares, and whatever else one may need

Thirdly - Our destination? To the Algerian coast - or the eastern shores of Africa. Take your pick.

And finally - Trust in the One and absolute.
